rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An establishment that delivers food from various restaurants to customers' homes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Delivery Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all diets. These are the restrictions and requirements of food. These restrictions and requirements can be of ingredients or preparation. A vegan diet, for example, excludes any animal products. A kosher diet excludes pork and shellfish and requires beef to be slaughtered in a specific manner.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Diet

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.diet to the mso:food.diet_follower that follows, or proclaims to follow, the diet. Note mso:food.diet_follower is deprecated, and this expected type should change to mso:people.person in the future.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Followers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:food.diet to the mso:food.recipe(s) that are appropriate to the diet.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recipes
follows_diet
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If this property is needed, it should be added to people.person. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for what type(s) of food may not be consumed. For example, a 'no dairy restriction' would preclude the consumption of milk, cheese, butter, and other cow and sheep milk products. This restriction would apply to a vegan diet, and the 'no meat restriction' would apply to both the vegan and vegetarian diet.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dietary Restriction

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
The dish type includes anything that is the end product of a recipe. A dish is ready to be served and eaten as a meal in itself or as part of a larger meal.
Things that are a dish:
## Dishes with a specific name (e.g. Beef Wellington, Quiche, Burrito, Conchinita Pibil, Risotto).
## Generally described dishes (e.g. Scrambled eggs, dry-fried beef with hefen, roasted goose).
## Salads (e.g. Tabouli, Caesar salad).
## Soups (e.g. hot and sour soup, minestrone, Manchow soup).
## Breads and pastries (e.g. peanut butter bun, Cheoreg, Chocolate brownie, Babka).
## Dessert dishes (e.g. Trifle, Halo-halo, Cranachan).
## End products of a recipe that are components of a larger dish such as sauces, dips, crusts (e.g. Bechamel sauce, salsa, pesto).
## Prepared or mixed drinks such as cocktails and coffee mixes (e.g. blue lagoon, singapore sling, latte, cappuccino).
Things that are not a Dish:
## Unprepared food such as fruits, vegetables or raw ingredients (e.g. apple, egg, pork belly) Use mso:food.food or one of its other subtypes for these cases.
## Recipes (e.g. Jeff???s oatmeal raisin cookies is a recipe of the dish Oatmeal raisin cookies). Use mso:food.recipe for these cases.
## Culinary techniques used in preparing dishes (e.g. braising, roasting). Use mso:food.culinary_technique for these.
## Types of dish (e.g. dessert, street food, convenience food). Use mso:food.type_of_dish for these.
## Types of cuisine (e.g. French cuisine, Chinese cuisine, Kosher). Use mso:food.cuisine for these.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dish

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.dish to its associated mso:food.cuisine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cuisine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.dish to the mso:food.ingredient(s) typically found in the dish. For example, avocado is a typical ingredient in guacamole.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ingredients

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.dish to a mso:food.recipe providing instructions to prepare a version of the dish.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recipes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a dish to the recommended temperature or temperature range, in degrees Celsius, for serving the dish.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Serving Temperature

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:food.dish to its mso:food.type_of_dish.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Type of Dish

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains things that are used to serve food and beverages, e.g. dinner plates, pasta bowls, and coffee mugs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dishware

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all drinking establishments. These are the businesses that serve alcoholic beverages and may also serve food, especially if require to do so by law, and other beverages.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Drinking Establishment

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.drinking_establishment to its mso:food.drinking_establishment_type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Drinking Establishment Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food_drinking_establishment to the licensing relationships for the establishment.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Licensee

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all drinking establishment type. These are the groupings of drinking establishments by common characteristics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Drinking Establishment Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:food.drinking_establishment_type to the mso:food.drinking_establishment(s) that are of this type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Establishments of This Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that contains dishware that is used to serve beverages, e.g. wine glasses and coffee mugs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Drinkware

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Food stores that specialize in selling food from a particular country or region, e.g. a Chinese or Indian grocery store.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ethnic Food Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in offering services to maintain the operation of farms. Includes farm hand services, crop dusting and spraying services, crop harvesting, farm equipment suppliers, and livestock dealers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Farm Service

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Street markets where local, independent vendors offer produce and prepared foods.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Farmers' Market

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An individual or business that specializes in the spawning and/or raising of fish, shellfish, and crustaceans.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fish Farm

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling various kinds of fish, especially fish that is expensive or difficult to obtain.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Fish Shop

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the substances consumed to provide nutritional support for the body. This includes whole foods, like almonds and chicken, as well as whole foods put together to make dishes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Food

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a food to a brand associated with the food.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Brand

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.food to the course in which it typically appears.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Course

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.food to the number of calories per 100 grams of the given food.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Energy

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.food to the amount of nutrients for a given quantity of a particular food. Note that this property (and its associated relationship type food.nutrition) are a generalization of food.food.nutrition_fact and food.nutrition_fact.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nutrition Information

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property that is used to express the amount of nutrients per 100 grams of the given food.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nutrition Fact

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.food to the region associated with the food. This can be the origin of the food, or a location otherwise deeply associated with the food.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Region

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a kind of food to a restaurant that serves the food.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Restaurant

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.food to the range of spiciness or pungency the food measures on the Scoville scale.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Scoville Scale

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating a food to a textual description of how the food is typically served, e.g. without ice, raw, grilled, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Served

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An unstructured representation of the serving size for the given food. Note that a food may have more than one serving size, since different organizations, e.g. government agencies and businesses, may have different notions about what constitutes an appropriate serving. Note too that this property should be used only when the value for the serving size cannot be expressed in a structured way via food.food.serving_size_structured.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Unstructured Serving Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A structured representation of the serving size for the given food. In cases where it is not possible to represent the serving size in a structured way, the property food.food.serving_size can be used, whose expected type is type.string.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Structured Serving Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property type relating a food type to its subtype. For example, "corn" has a subtype of "yellow corn" and "juice" has a subtype that includes "orange juice" and "carrot juice".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Food Subtype

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a food type to its supertype. For example, "yellow corn" has a supertype of "corn" and "Orange juice" has a supertype of "juice".
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Food Supertype

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.food to the USDA ID of an approximate match for the purposes of nutritional information.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: USDA Equivalent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.food to its USDA ID, the identification number assigned to the food by the US Department of Agriculture.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: USDA ID

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The type for qualifiers of food units in serving sizes, e.g. "medium" in the serving size of 1 medium egg.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Food Qualifier

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Any store or shop that offers raw or prepared food but is not a restaurant. This type includes grocery stores and supermarkets, but also butcher shops, cheese shops, and farmer's markets.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Food Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Stores that specialize in selling food that is relatively expensive and is widely regarded as sophisticated and/or creative.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Gourmet Food Store

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A farm that specializes in grain crops, such as wheat, corn, rice, soybean, and oats.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Grain Farm

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A kind of food that is used in a recipe to create a prepared food.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ingredient

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.ingredient to the mso:food.dietary_restriction the ingredient is compatible with. This means diets with the mso:food.dietary_restriction may include the ingredient in their foods. See also mso:food.ingredient.incompatible_with_dietary_restriction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Compatible with Dietary Restrictions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.ingredient to its associated mso:food.cuisine. For instance, tortillas and poblano chillis are associated with Mexican cuisine.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cuisine

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:food.ingredient to the mso:food.dish(es) in which the ingredient is typically used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dishes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.ingredient to the mso:food.dietary_restriction the ingredient is incompatible with. This means diets with the mso:food.dietary_restriction may *not* include the ingredient in their foods. See also mso:food.ingredient.compatible_with_dietary_restriction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Incompatible with dietary restrictions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.ingredient to its broader mso:food.ingredient. For example, 'bell pepper' has a supertype of 'pepper'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ingredient Supertype

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:food.ingredient to the mso:food.recipe_ingredient relationship collecting the data on an ingredient's use in a given recipe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recipes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data on the licensing for a given establishment. This type includes the dates of the licensing, the holder of the license, and the establishment.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Licensee Tenure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:food.licensee_tenure relationship to the mso:food.drinking_establishment the license covers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Drinking Establishment

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.licensee_tenure to the date the license relationship for the given establishment started.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.licensee_tenure to the mso:food.licensee that holds the liquor licenses for the given drinking establishment. Note that mso:food.licensee is deprecated, and this expected type should be changes to event.agent.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Licensee

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.licensee_tenure relationship to the date the relationship ended.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An alcoholic beverage that is prepared by mixing distilled spirits with other flavorings and liquids, e.g. citrus slices, juice, spices, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Mixed Drink

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A Boolean property that indicates that the mixed drink has been selected by the International Bartenders Association for preparation in the annual World Cocktail Competition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: IBA Official Cocktail

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links a mixed drink to drinkware that is typically used to serve the drink, e.g. a cocktail glass.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Drinkware

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a mixed drink to a food that is standardly used to embellish the drink, e.g. a slice of lemon or lime.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Garnish

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a mixed drink to the distilled spirit that is dominant by volume in the drink.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Primary Alcohol

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all nutrients. These are the components of food that organisms use to grow and live.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nutrient

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.nutrient to the mso:food.recommended_daily_value_type type that represents a recommended daily amount of the nutrient for good health.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recommended Daily Value

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.nutrient to its ID in the USDA's National Nutrient Database for Standard Reference.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: USDA ID

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A relationship type that is used to specify an amount of nutrient.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nutrition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the food for which the nutritional information is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Food

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the amount of the given food, expressed as a decimal.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Food Quantity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the unit of measure with which the quantity of the given food should be understood.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Food Unit

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the nutrient.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nutrient

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the percentage of one's daily requirement provided by the given amount of the given nutrient.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nutrient Daily Value Percent

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the amount of the given nutrient, expressed as a decimal.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nutrient Quantity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the unit of measure with which the quantity of the given nutrient should be understood.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nutrient Unit

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data on the nutrition facts for an entity. It includes the food, the nutrient in the food, and the nutrient's quantity per 100 grams of the given food.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nutrition Fact
IUs per 100g
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Redundant with food.nutrition.nutrient_unit and food.nutrition.nutrient_quantity. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:food.nutrition.nutrient_quantity]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Quantity per 100g
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Redundant with food.nutrition.nutrient_unit and food.nutrition.nutrient_quantity. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\jcoop] Successor:[food.nutrition.nutrient_quantity]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A farm that specializes in the growing of plants that produce fruits and nuts, such as apples, pears, oranges, bananas, cherries, lemons, tree nuts, peaches, and so on.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Orchard

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A farm that specializes in the breeding, raising and selling of poultry (chickens, turkeys, geese, ducks, etc.). Includes egg hatcheries and egg farmers.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Poultry Farm

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Type collecting the data for a preparation instruction. This includes the description of the instruction and its order.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Preparation instruction

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.preparation_instruction to the stage or group of the instruction. In many recipes, there may be more than one set of steps to make a component of the overall recipe. For example, a carrot cake recipe may have a set of preparation steps for the cake and another set of steps for the cream cheese frosting.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Preparation Grouping

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.preparation_instruction to the order of the instruction.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Rank

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all recipes. A recipe is a set of instructions that describes how to prepare a culinary dish.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recipe

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a recipe to a textual description of potential allergens that the recipe includes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Allergens

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Category name which recipe belongs to
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Category
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: No data and the property is underspecified. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recipe to its cooking time in minutes. This is only the time for the actual heating portion of the recipe, see also mso:food.recipe.preparation_time and mso:food.recipe.total_time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Cooking time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recipe to the mso:food.culinary_technique(s) used in the recipe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Techniques

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recipe to the text description of the recipe's difficulty.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Difficulty

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recipe to the mso:food.dish the recipe prepares.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dish

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recipe to the mso:food.culinary_tool used in the recipe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Equipment

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recipe to its different flavor profiles. These are the tastes or flavors associated with dishes made from this recipe. Descriptions can include 'sour', 'sweet', 'fruity', and 'fresh'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flavor Profile

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recipe to the mso:time.holiday the food is traditionally associated with, e.g. cranberry sauce for Thanksgiving.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Holiday

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a recipe to nutritional information about a given unit of food that is prepared according to the recipe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nutrition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recipe to its mso:food.nutrition_fact(s). Note this is a more specific property of mso:food.recipe.nutrition.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nutrition Information

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Directions for recipe
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Directions

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a recipe to the total amount of time, in minutes, that is required to complete the recipe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Preparation Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The person or other agent, eg. The Moosewood Collective, that is responsible for the recipe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Author

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The recipe collection (book, website, etc) that this recipe came from
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Part of recipe collection

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating a recipe to information about the ingredients required for the recipe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ingredients

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Ingredients required for this recipe. Put one ingredient per value, multiple ingredients in the same value are not allowed. Holds unparsed raw text (please use food.recipe.recipe_ingredient if structured data is available)
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ingredients

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: How many people would this recipe serve? For dishes like cookies, specify units.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Servings

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a recipe to a special diet for which the recipe is suitable, e.g. vegetarian, gluten-free, kosher, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Suitable for Diets

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The total amount of time in minutes required to make the given recipe. Note that this is food.recipe.preparation time plus food.recipe.cooking_time.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Total Time

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a recipe to a special diet for which the recipe is *not* suitable, e.g. vegetarian, gluten-free, kosher, etc.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Unsuitable for Diets

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a recipe to a video showing how to make the recipe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recipe Video

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a recipe to an action of viewing the recipe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: View Recipe
recipes
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: If this property is needed, it should be added to event.agent. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity type representing the collection of all recipe collections. A recipe collection is a set of recipes grouped together by any characteristic.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recipe Collection

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recipe collection to the mso:food.recipes in the collection.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recipes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data on an ingredient's use in a recipe. It includes the quantity, recipe, ingredient, and ingredient unit of measure. If the ingredient's data is unstructured or raw text, use type.object.description on this type. There should be one food.recipe_ingredient entity per ingredient for a recipe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recipe Ingredient

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recipe_ingredient to its grouping within a recipe. Many recipes have several stages and these different stages have different ingredients associates with them. For example, a carrot cake recipe will have ingredients like flour, butter, carrots, and sugar associated with the making of the cake, and for the icing stage may have cream cheese and sugar ingredients.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ingredient Grouping

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recipe_ingredient to the mso:food.ingredient used in the given recipe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ingredient

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Any additional information about the use or preparation of this ingredient.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Notes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recipe_ingredient to its order, either in the recipe or within a stage of the recipe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Order

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recipe_ingredient relationship to the amount of the ingredient used.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Quantity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:food.recipe_ingredient to the mso:food.recipe using the ingredient.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recipe

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property specifying information about the amount of the ingredient to be used in the given recipe. Note that this property is multivalued, because in some recipes an ingredient amount may be indicated in more than one way, e.g. as 1 cup or 8 ounces.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recipe Ingredient Amount

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recipe_ingredient relationship to the mso:food.culinary_measure for the quantity of the ingredient. For example, if a recipe calls for 1 cup of water, the quantity is "1" and the unit is "cup". This can also include approximate measures such as "pinch" and "handful."
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Unit

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the amount of an ingredient used in a particular recipe.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recipe Ingredient Amount

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a culinary measure, e.g. cup or tablespoon, for the given quantity. Note that either this property or mso:food.recipe_ingredient_amount.standard_measure, but not both, should be used for any instance of mso:food.recipe_ingredient_amount.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Culinary Measure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a numeric quantity for the given measure. Note that either this property or mso:food.recipe_ingredient_amount.quantity_range, but not both, should be used for any instance of mso:food.recipe_ingredient_amount.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Quantity

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a numeric quantity range for the given measure. Note that either this property or mso:food.recipe_ingredient_amount.quantity, but not both, should be used for any instance of mso:food.recipe_ingredient_amount.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Quantity Range

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies a standard measure, e.g. ounce, gram or liter, for the given quantity. Note that either this property or mso:food.recipe_ingredient_amount.culinary_measure, but not both, should be used for any instance of mso:food.recipe_ingredient_amount.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Standard Measure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Value type collecting data on an mso:food.nutrient's recommended daily value.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Recommended Daily Value

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recommended_daily_value_type to the unit used in the recommendation. Note that different recommendations have different units associated with them.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Unit

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.recommended_daily_value_type to the value of the nutient that is recommended.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Value

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting the data on a chef's association with a given association. It includes the dates of the association as well as the chef and the restaurant.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Restaurant Chef Association

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.restaurant_chef_association relationship to the mso:food.chef associated at a given time to the restaurant.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Chef

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.restaurant_chef_association to the date the association started.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.restaurant_chef_association relationship to the mso:local.restaurant for the association with the given chef.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Restaurant

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.restaurant_chef_association relationship to the date the association ended.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To Date

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that specializes in the manufacturing, distribution, selling, leasing or maintenance of restaurant equipment and supplies.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Restaurant Supply Company

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A value type that represents serving sizes of food in a structured way. For example, in the case of the serving sizes "1 slice" or "9 grams", the elements "1", "9", "slice", and "gram" are related to their corresponding foods with separate properties.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Structured Serving Size

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that links a serving size to a food that has the serving size.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Food

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: An additional description attached to the unit of food, e.g. "medium" in the serving size of 1 medium egg.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Food Qualifier

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The unit of food for foods that have this kind of serving size, e.g. "slice" in 1 slice of cheese or "pat" in 1 pat of butter.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Food Unit

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of food units or units of measure (depending on which property is used in the particular case) that make up the serving size, e.g. "9" in 9 grams of sugar or "1" in 1 pat of butter.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property linking a serving size to information about the nutrition in the serving size.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Nutrition

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The unit of measure for foods that have this kind of serving size, e.g. "gram" in 9 grams of sugar.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Unit of Measure

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Large grocery stores that typically sell other items as well.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Supermarket

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all teas. Tea is an aromatic beverage commonly prepared by pouring hot or boiling water over cured leaves of the tea plant, Camellia sinensis.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tea

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.tea to the mso:location.location where this tea is currently or has been traditionally grown.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Grown in

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.tea to its mso:food.tea_type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all tea types. These are the groupings of teas by common characteristics. Types of tea include 'black tea' and 'green tea'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tea Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:food.tea_type to the mso:food.tea(s) of this type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tea

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all types of dishes. These are the groupings of dishes that have similar characteristics.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Type of Dish

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:food.type_of_dish to the mso:food.dish(es) of that type.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Dishes

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all wine styles. These are the groupings of wine by flavor, color, or production method that the wines share.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wine Style

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Grape varieties that are permissible in this style. (Note that some styles may not have a strict requirement for composition, in which case this property should be left blank.)
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Grape varieties

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The location this style of wine is from. (Note that some styles may not have a place of origin requirement, in which case this property should be left blank.)
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Place of origin

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Wine vintages made in this style.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wines

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Virtual property relating an mso:food.wine_style to the mso:wine.type(s) that as associated. For example, port, a style of wine, is a type of fortified wine. Wine types are a broader categorization than wine styles.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wine Types
